{{Lunisolar November}} '''November 27''' is the 27th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} – the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and its day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} .
== Events == * {{ill|Bunmei (Japan)|ja|文明|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 14th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1483|ja|1483|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|January 6|ja|1月6日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The Muromachi shogunate and {{ill|Furukawa|ja|古河公方|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ’s {{ill|Ashikaga Narushi|ja|足利成氏|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} reached an accord that ended the internal strife (the {{ill|Kyōtoku no Ran|ja|享徳の乱|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) in the Kantō region which had persisted since 1455. * {{ill|Tenmon (era)|ja|天文|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 18th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1549|ja|1549|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 15|ja|12月15日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The Matsudaira domain of Mikawa fell under the control of {{ill|Imagawa Yoshimoto|ja|今川義元|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , and Takechiyo (later known as {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|ja|徳川家康|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) was sent as a hostage to Sunpu. * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 10th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1828|ja|1828|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|January 13|ja|1月13日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Ienari|ja|徳川家斉|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} built a gate ({{ill|Omamiden|ja|御守殿門|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , now the red gate of the University of Tokyo’s Hongo campus) on the estate of the Maeda clan in Kaga. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1855|ja|1855|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|January 15|ja|1月15日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Kaien|ja|嘉永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1872|ja|1872|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|December 27|ja|12月27日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – A notice was issued by the Daijōkan for non-payment of salaries for December.
== Births == * {{ill|Kōji (Japan)|ja|Kōji|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1556|ja|1556|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|January 8|ja|1月8日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Uesugi Kagekatsu|ja|上杉景勝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , a daimyō († {{ill|1623|ja|1623|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
