== Events == * {{ill|Bunmei (Japan)|ja|文明}} 14th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} {{ill|1483|ja|1483}} {{ill|January 6|ja|1月6日}} ) – The Muromachi shogunate and {{ill|Furukawa|ja|古河公方}} ’s {{ill|Ashikaga Narushi|ja|足利成氏}} reached an accord that ended the internal strife (the {{ill|Kyōtoku no Ran|ja|享徳の乱}} ) in the Kantō region which had persisted since 1455. * {{ill|Tenmon (era)|ja|天文}} 18th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} {{ill|1549|ja|1549}} {{ill|December 15|ja|12月15日}} ) – The Matsudaira domain of Mikawa fell under the control of {{ill|Imagawa Yoshimoto|ja|今川義元}} , and Takechiyo (later known as {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|ja|徳川家康}} ) was sent as a hostage to Sunpu. * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政}} 10th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1828|ja|1828}} {{ill|January 13|ja|1月13日}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Ienari|ja|徳川家斉}} built a gate ({{ill|Omamiden|ja|御守殿門}} , now the red gate of the University of Tokyo’s Hongo campus) on the estate of the Maeda clan in Kaga. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|1855|ja|1855}} {{ill|January 15|ja|1月15日}} ) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Kaien|ja|嘉永}} to {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政}} 