{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十一月廿七|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 11월 27일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar November|qq=}} '''November 27''' is the 27th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=}} – the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . Its Rokuyō is {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=}} and its day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=}} .
== Events == * {{ill|Bunmei (Japan)|ja|文明|qq=}} 14th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|1483|ja|1483|qq=}} {{ill|January 6|ja|1月6日|qq=}} ) – The Muromachi shogunate and {{ill|Furukawa|ja|古河公方|qq=}} ’s {{ill|Ashikaga Narushi|ja|足利成氏|qq=}} reached an accord that ended the internal strife (the {{ill|Kyōtoku no Ran|ja|享徳の乱|qq=}} ) in the Kantō region which had persisted since 1455. * {{ill|Tenmon (era)|ja|天文|qq=}} 18th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|1549|ja|1549|qq=}} {{ill|December 15|ja|12月15日|qq=}} ) – The Matsudaira domain of Mikawa fell under the control of {{ill|Imagawa Yoshimoto|ja|今川義元|qq=}} , and Takechiyo (later known as {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|ja|徳川家康|qq=}} ) was sent as a hostage to Sunpu. * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|qq=}} 10th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1828|ja|1828|qq=}} {{ill|January 13|ja|1月13日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Ienari|ja|徳川家斉|qq=}} built a gate ({{ill|Omamiden|ja|御守殿門|qq=}} , now the red gate of the University of Tokyo’s Hongo campus) on the estate of the Maeda clan in Kaga. * {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|qq=}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1855|ja|1855|qq=}} {{ill|January 15|ja|1月15日|qq=}} ) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Kaien|ja|嘉永|qq=}} to {{ill|Ansei|ja|安政|qq=}} . * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1872|ja|1872|qq=}} {{ill|December 27|ja|12月27日|qq=}} ) – A notice was issued by the Daijōkan for non-payment of salaries for December.
== Births == * {{ill|Kōji (Japan)|ja|Kōji|qq=}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|1556|ja|1556|qq=}} {{ill|January 8|ja|1月8日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Uesugi Kagekatsu|ja|上杉景勝|qq=}} , a daimyō († {{ill|1623|ja|1623|qq=}} ).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Ōchō|ja|応長|qq=}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|1311|ja|1311|qq=}} {{ill|November 3|ja|11月3日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Hojo Ujitoki|ja|北条師時|qq=}} , the 10th shikken of the Kamakura shogunate (* {{ill|1275|ja|1275|qq=}} ). * {{ill|An'ei|ja|安永|qq=}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1773|ja|1773|qq=}} {{ill|October 22|ja|10月22日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Tanuma Iamasa|ja|田沼意明|qq=}} , the first lord of the Mutsu Shimomura domain (* {{ill|1796|ja|1796|qq=}} ). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|qq=}} 12th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}} {{ill|1829|ja|1829|qq=}} {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日|qq=}} ) – The 4th generation leader of {{ill|Tsuruyanin|ja|鶴屋南北|qq=}} , a kabuki dramatist (* {{ill|1755|ja|1755|qq=}} ).
