== Events == * [[:en:Civilization|Bunmei (Japan)]] 14th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|1483|ja|1483|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1483|qq=}} [[:en:January 6|January 6]] ) – The Muromachi shogunate and {{ill|Furukawa|ja|古河公方|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Furukawa|qq=}} ’s [[:en:Ashikaga Shigeuji|Ashikaga Narushi]] reached an accord that ended the internal strife (the [[:en:Kyōtoku incident|Kyōtoku no Ran]] ) in the Kantō region which had persisted since 1455. * {{ill|Tenmon (era)|ja|天文|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmon (era)|qq=}} 18th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|1549|ja|1549|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1549|qq=}} [[:en:December 15|December 15]] ) – The Matsudaira domain of Mikawa fell under the control of [[:en:Imagawa Yoshimoto|Imagawa Yoshimoto]] , and Takechiyo (later known as [[:en:Tokugawa Ieyasu|Tokugawa Ieyasu]] ) was sent as a hostage to Sunpu. * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 10th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1828|ja|1828|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1828|qq=}} [[:en:January 13|January 13]] ) – [[:en:Tokugawa Ienari|Tokugawa Ienari]] built a gate ({{ill|Omamiden|ja|御守殿門|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Omamiden|qq=}} , now the red gate of the University of Tokyo’s Hongo campus) on the estate of the Maeda clan in Kaga. * [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1855|ja|1855|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1855|qq=}} [[:en:January 15|January 15]] ) – The era name was changed from [[:en:Kaei|Kaien]] to [[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] . * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1872|ja|1872|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1872|qq=}} [[:en:December 27|December 27]] ) – A notice was issued by the Daijōkan for non-payment of salaries for December.
== Births == * {{ill|Kōji (Japan)|1=Kōji (Muromachi period)|2=ja|3=弘治 (日本)|lt=Kōji|4=ru|5=Кодзи (Муромати)|ja|Kōji|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōji (Japan)|1=Kōji (Muromachi period)|2=ja|3=弘治 (日本)|lt=Kōji|4=ru|5=Кодзи (Муромати)|qq=}} 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|1556|ja|1556|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1556|qq=}} [[:en:January 8|January 8]] ) – [[:en:Uesugi Kagekatsu|Uesugi Kagekatsu]] , a daimyō († {{ill|1623|ja|1623|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1623|qq=}} ).
