== Events ==
* {{ill|Civilization|en|Civilization|WD=Q8432|lt=Bunmei (Japan)|1=Civilization}} 14th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}}  {{ill|1483|en|1483|WD=Q6637|lt=1483|1=1483}}  {{ill|January 6|en|January 6|WD=Q2221|lt=January 6|1=January 6}} ) – The Muromachi shogunate and {{ill|Furukawa|ja|古河公方|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Furukawa|1=Koga kubō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q8017022}} ’s {{ill|Ashikaga Shigeuji|en|Ashikaga Shigeuji|WD=Q4306913|lt=Ashikaga Narushi|1=Ashikaga Shigeuji}}  reached an accord that ended the internal strife (the {{ill|Kyōtoku incident|en|Kyōtoku incident|WD=Q6453098|lt=Kyōtoku no Ran|1=Kyōtoku incident}} ) in the Kantō region which had persisted since 1455.
* {{ill|Tenmon (era)|ja|天文|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmon (era)|1=Tenmon|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q21096812}} 18th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}}  {{ill|1549|en|1549|WD=Q6554|lt=1549|1=1549}}  {{ill|December 15|en|December 15|WD=Q2383|lt=December 15|1=December 15}} ) – The Matsudaira domain of Mikawa fell under the control of {{ill|Imagawa Yoshimoto|en|Imagawa Yoshimoto|WD=Q1054305|lt=Imagawa Yoshimoto|1=Imagawa Yoshimoto}} , and Takechiyo (later known as {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyasu|en|Tokugawa Ieyasu|WD=Q171977|lt=Tokugawa Ieyasu|1=Tokugawa Ieyasu}} ) was sent as a hostage to Sunpu.
* {{ill|Bunsei|en|Bunsei|WD=Q1327119|lt=Bunsei|1=Bunsei}} 10th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}}  {{ill|1828|en|1828|WD=Q7570|lt=1828|1=1828}}  {{ill|January 13|en|January 13|WD=Q2255|lt=January 13|1=January 13}} ) – {{ill|Tokugawa Ienari|en|Tokugawa Ienari|WD=Q439717|lt=Tokugawa Ienari|1=Tokugawa Ienari}}  built a gate ({{ill|Omamiden|ja|御守殿門|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Omamiden|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 御守殿|1=Akamon (Tokyo)|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q48807898}} , now the red gate of the University of Tokyo’s Hongo campus) on the estate of the Maeda clan in Kaga.
* {{ill|Ansei|en|Ansei|WD=Q1327259|lt=Ansei|1=Ansei}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}}  {{ill|1855|en|1855|WD=Q7673|lt=1855|1=1855}}  {{ill|January 15|en|January 15|WD=Q2260|lt=January 15|1=January 15}} ) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Kaei|en|Kaei|WD=Q1146125|lt=Kaien|1=Kaei}}  to {{ill|Ansei|en|Ansei|WD=Q1327259|lt=Ansei|1=Ansei}} .
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|WD=Q3125096|lt=Meiji era|1=Meiji era}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}}  {{ill|1872|en|1872|WD=Q7753|lt=1872|1=1872}}  {{ill|December 27|en|December 27|WD=Q2800|lt=December 27|1=December 27}} ) – A notice was issued by the Daijōkan for non-payment of salaries for December.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Kōji (Muromachi period)|en|Kōji (Muromachi period)|WD=Q1143910|lt=Kōji|1=Kōji (Muromachi period)}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}}  {{ill|1556|en|1556|WD=Q6590|lt=1556|1=1556}}  {{ill|January 8|en|January 8|WD=Q2234|lt=January 8|1=January 8}} ) – {{ill|Uesugi Kagekatsu|en|Uesugi Kagekatsu|WD=Q1376605|lt=Uesugi Kagekatsu|1=Uesugi Kagekatsu}} , a daimyō († {{ill|1623|en|1623|WD=Q6818|lt=1623|1=1623}} ).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Ōchō|en|Ōchō|WD=Q1327136|lt=Ōchō|1=Ōchō}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}}  {{ill|1311|en|1311|WD=Q5731|lt=1311|1=1311}}  {{ill|November 3|en|November 3|WD=Q2995|lt=November 3|1=November 3}} ) – {{ill|Hōjō Morotoki|en|Hōjō Morotoki|WD=Q2672978|lt=Hojo Ujitoki|1=Hōjō Morotoki}} , the 10th shikken of the Kamakura shogunate (* {{ill|1275|en|1275|WD=Q5529|lt=1275|1=1275}} ).
* {{ill|An'ei|ja|安永|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/An'ei|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 安永 (元号)|1=An'ei|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q1193910}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}}  {{ill|1773|en|1773|WD=Q7692|lt=1773|1=1773}}  {{ill|October 22|en|October 22|WD=Q2957|lt=October 22|1=October 22}} ) – {{ill|Tanuma Iamasa|ja|田沼意明|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanuma Iamasa|1=Tanuma Okiaki|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q6635782}} , the first lord of the Mutsu Shimomura domain (* {{ill|1796|en|1796|WD=Q7818|lt=1796|1=1796}} ).
* {{ill|Bunsei|en|Bunsei|WD=Q1327119|lt=Bunsei|1=Bunsei}} 12th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}}  {{ill|1829|en|1829|WD=Q7572|lt=1829|1=1829}}  {{ill|December 22|en|December 22|WD=Q2636|lt=December 22|1=December 22}} ) – The 4th generation leader of {{ill|Tsuruyanin|ja|鶴屋南北|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuruyanin|1=Tsuruya Namboku|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q1675237}} , a kabuki dramatist (* {{ill|1755|en|1755|WD=Q7627|lt=1755|1=1755}} ).

